    <p>Contrary to playing characters is simply existing.</p>
    <p>A concept many people find terrifying, if not completely illogical.</p>
    <p>Part of the reason is because when we're so deeply in character, it becomes almost impossible to relate to the world without character.</p>
    <p>This signifies the attachment we have with these characters, and so we associate 'simply existing' with the depression and loneliness of not being in character.</p>
    <p>In other words, simply existing is living without attachment.</p>
    <p>What people in character don't realise is that attachment is what is making them feel depressed and lonely, not existence.</p>
